						<summary>

						<p>Stone kept in front of the Sitārāmasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 12[23], Plavaṅga Kārttika [śu 11], Friday, Śatabhisha</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1301 A.D., October 13.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of some lands under cultivation of Kāmasamudram (a tank of Kanuparṭi) for defraying the expenses of worship and offerings to the god Malamaṇḍalaperumāḷ of Mōṭṭupalli by Kāmaya-bōya. Published; <hi rend="italic">NDI,</hi> Part II, No. 54.</p>						

						</summary>
